'''Gustavo Raúl Gómez Portillo''' (born 6 May 1993) is a Paraguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] both [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

==Club career==

===Lanús===
Gómez is considered one of the most promising defenders of Paraguay, who began his playing career at [[Club Libertad|Libertad]]. In the summer of 2014, Gómez left [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] to play for [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Club Atlético Lanús|Lanús]].<ref>[http://www.clublanus.com/futbol/profesional/noticia/id/6929 Gustavo Gómez es el segundo refuerzo (Gustavo Gómez is the second reinforcement)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714195021/http://www.clublanus.com/futbol/profesional/noticia/id/6929 |date=2014-07-14 }} Club Lanus. 29 June 2014. {{in lang|es}}</ref> Gustavo Gomez's Lanus conceded a mere 10 goals in 17 games en route to securing 2016 Argentine Primera Division title.

===AC Milan===
On 5 August 2016, Gómez completed a move to [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] for a fee reported to be in the region of €8.5 million, signing a 5-year contract.<ref>[https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/club/2016-08-05/welcome-gustavo-gomez Welcome Gustavo Gomez! | AC Milan] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808161042/http://www.acmilan.com/en/news/club/2016-08-05/welcome-gustavo-gomez |date=2016-08-08 }} www.acmilan.com. 5 August 2016</ref> He is the first ever Paraguayan footballer to play for Milan. After joining the club he chose number 15, in tribute of his former [[Club Atlético Lanús|Lanús]] teammate, [[Diego Barisone]] who died in a car accident. 
<ref>http://www.ilmilanista.it/gazzanet/milan-gustavo-gomez-potrebbe-indossare-la-maglia-numero-15/?refresh_ce-cp {{Dead link|date=February 2022}}</ref>
On 27 August 2016, he made his full debut for Milan in [[Serie A]] against [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]], where Napoli beat Milan 4–2.

===Palmeiras===
[[File:Gustavo-Gomez-Palmeiras-Sao-Paulo-ago24.jpg|thumb|left|170px|Gómez com o Palmeiras em 2024]]
On 2 August 2018, Gómez transferred to [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] on loan with the option of purchase. Being considered by supporters as one of the best centerbacks of Palmeiras' history, he helped the team achieve three [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Brasileirão]] titles in 2018, 2022, and 2023, two [[Copa Libertadores]] trophies in 2020 and 2021, four [[Campeonato Paulista]] victories in 2020, 2022, 2023 and 2024 one [[Recopa Sudamericana]] in 2022, one [[Copa do Brasil]] in 2020 and one [[Supercopa do Brasil]] in 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/milan/?action=read&idtmw=1141845|access-date=3 August 2018|title=Ufficiale: Milan, ceduto Gustavo Gomez al Palmeiras|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803163506/https://m.tuttomercatoweb.com/milan/?action=read&idtmw=1141845|archive-date=3 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

In June 2024, Gómez reached the mark of 37 goals scored with the alviverde shirt, with this, he became the defender with the most goals in the history of Palmeiras, surpassing [[Luís Pereira]].<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Cristo |first=Gisele Vitória da Silva |date=2024-11-19 |title=Racismo No Futebol Brasileiro: Uma Análise da Legislação Acerca Das Questões Raciais No Futebol Brasilero |url=https://doi.org/10.69849/revistaft/fa10202411191355 |journal=RevistaFT |volume=29 |issue=140 |pages=55–56 |doi=10.69849/revistaft/fa10202411191355 |issn=1678-0817|url-access=subscription }}</ref>

==International career==
Gustavo's first selection to the Paraguay national team was for a friendly against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in August 2013.<ref>{{usurped|1=[https://web.archive.org/web/20140427010857/http://www.seleccionparaguaya.org/amistoso-vs-alemania-14-08-2013-c32 Convocatoria Amistoso vs. Alemania (14-08-2013)]}} Selección Paraguaya de Fútbol. {{in lang|es}}</ref> On 7 September 2013, he debuted against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] at the age of 20, and in that game he scored his first international goal. He played in the four editions of Copa América (Centenario, 2019, 2021, and 2024), having been the captain of the Paraguayan national team in the first two editions.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=258419/match=300180947/index.html FIFA World Cup Brazil: Paraguay-Bolivia – Overview]. {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613004157/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=258419/match=300180947/index.html |date=2017-06-13 }}. FIFA.com. 6 September 2013.</ref>

==Style of play==
Gómez is a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] known for his feisty style of play and for his leadership skills. He is a defender who excels in defense, aerial play, and tackling, but is also capable of contributing to playmaking.<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=BARROSO FURTADO |first=ENRICO |title=O IMPACTO DA ECONOMIA NO FUTEBOL ARGENTINO EM COMPARAÇÃO AO FUTEBOL BRASILEIRO |date=2023 |publisher=Faculdades Catolicas |doi=10.17771/pucrio.acad.70828 |url=https://doi.org/10.17771/pucrio.acad.70828|url-access=subscription }}</ref> He prioritizes defensive quality and physical strength, qualities that have made him one of the best defenders in South American football and an idol at Palmeiras, where he is captain.
<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Gómez-Polo |first1=Cristina |last2=Gómez-Polo |first2=Miguel |last3=Quispe López |first3=Norberto |last4=Portillo Muñoz |first4=Maria |last5=Montero |first5=Javier |date=2022-03-21 |title=3D Master Toothguide Is Adequate to Subjective Shade Selection? |journal=Medicina |volume=58 |issue=3 |pages=457 |doi=10.3390/medicina58030457 |doi-access=free |issn=1648-9144|pmc=8954102 }}</ref>

